description: German Chancellor Angela Merkel and French President François Hollande said they would continue to support the European Union on closer relations with Ukraine despite the Dutch voting against a referendum agreement this week.
title: Merkel and Hollande on Dutch Referendum
title_page: Merkel and Hollande on Dutch Referendum - Video - NYTimes.com
text: German Chancellor Angela Merkel and French President François Hollande said they would continue to support the European Union on closer relations with Ukraine despite the Dutch voting against a referendum agreement this week.
